title: Jordan Food Inflation
description: Cost of food in Jordan increased 3.05 percent in September of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Food Inflation in Jordan averaged 2.25 percent from 1999 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 29.30 percent in September of 2008 and a record low of -15.31 percent in February of 2004. This page provides the latest reported value for - Jordan Food Inflation - plus previous releases, historical high and low, short-term forecast and long-term prediction, economic calendar, survey consensus and news.
author: The Hashemite Kingdom of Jordan Department of Statistics (DOS)
